  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Northern Evacuation Shelters through Pan American Development Foundation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to rehabilitate and upgrade 19 evacuation shelters in identified communes in the Great North with the goal to reduce community vulnerability to external shocks through physical infrastructure and mitigation measures. The Specific objectives include:

- To ensure access to safer evacuation shelters in communities vulnerable to the adverse effects of disasters
- To ensure active community participation and mobilization of local resources, both human and material, to support the growth of the local economical market</narrative>
  </description>
